wikipedia_page.main: Arthur Gilbert de Laval Willis (25 August 1893 – 5 April 1979) was an Anglican clergyman and British athlete. He competed in the men's high jump at the 1924 Summer Olympics.

response: Arthur Willis had joined the Royal Navy the day before World War I and after the war joined  Royal Tank Corps. He was the army high jump champion and represented his country at high jump in the 1924 Olympic games. He completed his MA degree at Cambridge and took over the school in 1927. Ascham St. Vincent's prospered, with leavers spassing entrance exams to public schools of their choice and winning scholarships to Eton, Malvern and Eastbourne colleges. In 1938  Willis was worried about the threatening situation in Europe. He returned to the Royal Tank Corps and closed and sold the school.
